<collectingCountry id="0B8637B1FFCCFFCFFE4D24F8D888F999" box="[479,646,1523,1549]" name="United States of America" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">United States</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
(Arizona, California, Nevada).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFCCFFCFFEAA2710DF10F9CA" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFCCFFCFFEAA2710DF10F9CA" blockId="27.[264,1326,284,1630]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFCCFFCFFEAA2710DBB3F9A1" bold="true" box="[312,445,1563,1589]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet derives from the Greek “ ” = small; referring to the relatively small size of this species as compared to most species in this region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
